<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <title>Localizer Doc</title>
        <meta name="description" content="Hakkapedia">
        <meta name="author" content="Hakkapedia">
        <style type="text/css">
        
            {css}
            
            section {
                padding: 0 0 40px 0;
            }
            .sub-title {
                margin: 15px 0 0 0;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            
            <div class="page-header">
                <h1>Localizer <small>documentation</small></h1>
            </div>
            
            <section id="access">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="span3">
                        <h2>Using the API</h2>
                        <p>The localizer provides several ways for fetching data.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span9">
                        
                        <h3>Endpoint</h3>
                        <p>{host}/api/get</p>
                        
                        <h3>Parameters</h3>
                        <table class="table table-bordered">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>parameter</th>
                                    <th>Values</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>lang</td>
                                    <td>Any valid language prefix like <strong>fi</strong> or <strong>se</strong> for example. By default the value of this parameter is <strong>@all</strong></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>categories</td>
                                    <td>Any valid <strong>id</strong> of category. You could pass many categories by separating them with <strong>commas(,)</strong> . It is possible to pass <strong>@all</strong> as parameter to receive all the added categories together with their added translations.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>keys</td>
                                    <td>Any valid <strong>uid</strong> of translation. You could pass many translations by separating them with <strong>commas(,)</strong> . It is possible to pass <strong>@all</strong> as parameter to receive all the added translations.</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        
                        <h3>Examples</h3>
                        <a href="{host}/api/get?categories=3,2&lang=se" target="_blank">{host}/api/get?categories=3,2&amp;lang=se</a><br />
                        <a href="{host}/api/get?keys=main-menu-button2,new-translation" target="_blank">{host}/api/get?keys=main-menu-button2,new-translation</a>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="access">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="span3">
                        <h2>Pinging</h2>
                        <p>The localizer offers a possibility to ping some url defined by you and send a data to it. The pinging works when some new translation is added or an existence is edited. So, to receive a ping just open and save some of the current made records.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span9">
                        
                        <h3>Add your url in the localizer</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Log in</li>
                            <li>Go to <a href="{host}/admin/categories">{host}/admin/categories</a></li>
                            <li>Click the <strong>Edit</strong> icon next to the category which you want to setup</li>
                            <li>
                                Click <strong>Add</strong> in <strong>API calls</strong> section<br />
                                Location to ping - your url<br />
                                Lang - fi, se, no ...<br />
                                Compress - set <strong>1</strong> if <strong>gzuncompress</strong> php method is available on your server
                            </li>                            
                        </ul>
                        
                        <h3>Setup the necessary files on your server</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Download the helper class - <a href="{host}/pinger/LocalizerPinger.zip">LocalizerPinger</a></li>
                            <li>
                                Usage of the class
<pre>
require("LocalizerPinger.php");
$pinger = new LocalizerPinger();
// $pinger->error is an object if there is any error
if(!$pinger->error) { 
    // $pinger->data - contains all the translations send by the localizer
    // $pinger->roughData - contains translations in JSON format
    file_put_contents("your_translations.json", json_encode($pinger->data));
}
</pre>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            
        </div>
    </body>
</html>